The paper deals with online learning, which is a subfield of machine learning, and specifically focuses on distributed online learning with privacy preservation. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also involves communication networks and privacy, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses privacy-preserving properties, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
